cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about improving the performance of Residual Convolutional Neural Networks (ResNet) in visual recognition tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a new method for deriving weight values for the mapping units based on the input data, which involves using fully connected layers to estimate the weights. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), which are all related to the development of machine learning algorithms. Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on various datasets, which suggests that it may also belong to the category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
